text.tspan: SPI.3 signals appearing on IO Multiplexing table in datasheet (PA0:MOSI.3, PA1:MISO.3, PC1:SS.3) are incorrect, per MCP case #01057955
The notation SDA.3 means Wire.swap(3). You must choose SDA.3 and SCL.3 or SDA.2 and SCL.2 together. Each peripheral can have only
one swap position set. Signals are often suffixed by the peripheral number so RX1 is UART1 rx. In a few cases n,FN is used (2,OUT.1).
The notation SDAs.3/SCLs.3 is where the slave pins are in dual mode. Data from AVR32DD20 dfp.2.1.152. Diagrams by ObviousInRetrospect.
